dlinkSwDot1xExtMIB.name: dlinkSwDot1xExtMIB

revisions.description: This is the first version of the MIB file for IEEE 802.1X extensions.

dlinkSwDot1xExtMIB.contactinfo: D-Link Corporation Postal: No. 289, Sinhu 3rd Rd., Neihu District, Taipei City 114, Taiwan, R.O.C Tel: +886-2-66000123 E-mail: tsd@dlink.com.tw
dlinkSwDot1xExtMIB.description: This MIB module defines objects for managing IEEE 802.1X extensions which cannot be covered by standard MIB (IEEE8021-PAE-MIB).

dDot1xExtClearCounterByIf.name: dDot1xExtClearCounterByIf
dDot1xExtClearCounterByIf.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the interface on which 802.1X authentication and session statistics will be cleared. When read, a value of 0 is returned.

dDot1xExtInitByMacAddr.name: dDot1xExtInitByMacAddr
dDot1xExtInitByMacAddr.description: This object specifies a MAC address which will be initialized. When read, a value of '000000000000'H is returned.

dDot1xExtReAuthByMacAddr.name: dDot1xExtReAuthByMacAddr
dDot1xExtReAuthByMacAddr.description: This object specifies a MAC address which will be re-authenticated. When read, a value of '000000000000'H is returned.

dDot1xExtNotifEnabled.name: dDot1xExtNotifEnabled
dDot1xExtNotifEnabled.description: Setting to 'true' to enable global SNMP notification for 802.1X authentication feature. Setting the object to 'false' will disable SNMP notifications.

dDot1xExtPaePortTable.name: dDot1xExtPaePortTable
dDot1xExtPaePortTable.description: A table contains a list of port-specific information for the 802.1X extensions.

dDot1xExtPaePortEntry.name: dDot1xExtPaePortEntry
dDot1xExtPaePortEntry.description: An entry in dDot1xExtPaePortTable indicates per port 802.1X extensions information which is not covered by IEEE8021-PAE-MIB.

dDot1xExtPaePortNumber.name: dDot1xExtPaePortNumber
dDot1xExtPaePortNumber.description: This object indicates the ifIndex of the port.

dDot1xExtPaePortEnabled.name: dDot1xExtPaePortEnabled
dDot1xExtPaePortEnabled.description: This object is used to enable/disable IEEE 802.1X port access entity (PAE) authenticator.

dDot1xExtPaePortForwardPdu.name: dDot1xExtPaePortForwardPdu
dDot1xExtPaePortForwardPdu.description: This object is used to enable/disable forwarding of IEEE 802.1X PDU. 'true' indicates the forwarding of 802.1X PDU is enabled. 'false' indicates the forwarding of 802.1X PDU is disabled.

dDot1xExtAuthStatsTable.name: dDot1xExtAuthStatsTable
dDot1xExtAuthStatsTable.description: A table that contains the statistics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port/MAC/VLAN (for multi-auth mode).

dDot1xExtAuthStatsEntry.name: dDot1xExtAuthStatsEntry
dDot1xExtAuthStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE, including multi-auth mode.

dDot1xExtAuthStatsMacAddr.name: dDot1xExtAuthStatsMacAddr
dDot1xExtAuthStatsMacAddr.description: This object indicates the MAC address of the entry.

dDot1xExtAuthStatsVlanId.name: dDot1xExtAuthStatsVlanId
dDot1xExtAuthStatsVlanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the entry.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAPOL frames of any type that have been received by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolFramesTx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolFramesTx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolFramesTx.description: The number of EAPOL frames of any type that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolStartFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolStartFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolStartFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Start frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolLogoffFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL Logoff frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolRespIdFramesRx.description: The number of EAP Resp/Id frames that have been received by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolRespFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolRespFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolRespFramesRx.description: The number of valid EAP Response frames (other than Resp/Id frames) that have been received by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolReqIdFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Req/Id frames that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthEapolReqFramesTx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapolReqFramesTx
dDot1xExtAuthEapolReqFramesTx.description: The number of EAP Request frames (other than Rq/Id frames) that have been transmitted by this Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthInvalidEapolFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the frame type is not recognized.

dDot1xExtAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthEapLengthErrorFramesRx.description: The number of EAPOL frames that have been received by this Authenticator in which the Packet Body Length field is invalid.

dDot1xExtAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.name: dDot1xExtAuthLastEapolFrameVersion
dDot1xExtAuthLastEapolFrameVersion.description: The protocol version number carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

dDot1xExtAuthLastEapolFrameSource.name: dDot1xExtAuthLastEapolFrameSource
dDot1xExtAuthLastEapolFrameSource.description: The source MAC address carried in the most recently received EAPOL frame.

dDot1xExtAuthDiagTable.name: dDot1xExtAuthDiagTable
dDot1xExtAuthDiagTable.description: A table that contains the diagnostics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port/MAC/VLAN (for multi-auth mode).

dDot1xExtAuthDiagEntry.name: dDot1xExtAuthDiagEntry
dDot1xExtAuthDiagEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE, including multi-auth mode.

dDot1xExtAuthDiagMacAddr.name: dDot1xExtAuthDiagMacAddr
dDot1xExtAuthDiagMacAddr.description: This object indicates the MAC address of the entry.

dDot1xExtAuthDiagVlanId.name: dDot1xExtAuthDiagVlanId
dDot1xExtAuthDiagVlanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the entry.

dDot1xExtAuthEntersConnecting.name: dDot1xExtAuthEntersConnecting
dDot1xExtAuthEntersConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions to the CONNECTING state from any other state.

dDot1xExtAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.name: dDot1xExtAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting
dDot1xExtAuthEapLogoffsWhileConnecting.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to DISCONNECTED as a result of receiving an EAPOL-Logoff message.

dDot1xExtAuthEntersAuthenticating.name: dDot1xExtAuthEntersAuthenticating
dDot1xExtAuthEntersAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from CONNECTING to AUTHENTICATING, as a result of an EAP-Response/Identity message being received from the Supplicant.

dDot1xExtAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticat.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticating
dDot1xExtAuthAuthSuccessWhileAuthenticat.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to AUTHENTICATED, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating successful authentication of the Supplicant (authSuccess = TRUE).

dDot1xExtAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthentica.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthenticating
dDot1xExtAuthAuthTimeoutsWhileAuthentica.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication timeout (authTimeout = TRUE).

dDot1xExtAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating
dDot1xExtAuthAuthFailWhileAuthenticating.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to HELD, as a result of the Backend Authentication state machine indicating authentication failure (authFail = TRUE).

dDot1xExtAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticat.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticating
dDot1xExtAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticat.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthentic.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticating
dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthentic.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthentic.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticating
dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthentic.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATING to ABORTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

dDot1xExtAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticat.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticated
dDot1xExtAuthAuthReauthsWhileAuthenticat.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of a reauthentication request (reAuthenticate = TRUE).

dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthentic.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthenticated
dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapStartsWhileAuthentic.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to CONNECTING, as a result of an EAPOL-Start message being received from the Supplicant.

dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthentic.name: dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthenticated
dDot1xExtAuthAuthEapLogoffWhileAuthentic.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine transitions from AUTHENTICATED to DISCONNECTED, as a result of an EAPOL-Logoff message being received from the Supplicant.

dDot1xExtAuthBackendResponses.name: dDot1xExtAuthBackendResponses
dDot1xExtAuthBackendResponses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an initial Access-Request packet to the Authentication server (i.e., executes sendRespToServer on entry to the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authenticator attempted communication with the Authentication Server.

dDot1xExtAuthBackendAccessChallenges.name: dDot1xExtAuthBackendAccessChallenges
dDot1xExtAuthBackendAccessChallenges.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an initial Access-Challenge packet from the Authentication server (i.e., aReq becomes TRUE, causing exit from the RESPONSE state). Indicates that the Authentication Server has communication with the Authenticator.

dDot1xExtAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSuppl.name: dDot1xExtAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSupplicant
dDot1xExtAuthBackendOtherRequestsToSuppl.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine sends an EAP-Request packet (other than an Identity, Notification, Failure or Success message) to the Supplicant (i.e., executes txReq on entry to the REQUEST state). Indicates that the Authenticator chose an EAP-method.

dDot1xExtAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromS.name: dDot1xExtAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromSupplicant
dDot1xExtAuthBackendNonNakResponsesFromS.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives a response from the Supplicant to an initial EAP-Request, and the response is something other than EAP-NAK (i.e., rxResp becomes TRUE, causing the state machine to transition from REQUEST to RESPONSE, and the response is not an EAP-NAK). Indicates that the Supplicant can respond to the Authenticator's chosen EAP-method.

dDot1xExtAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.name: dDot1xExtAuthBackendAuthSuccesses
dDot1xExtAuthBackendAuthSuccesses.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Success message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aSuccess becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to SUCCESS). Indicates that the Supplicant has successfully authenticated to the Authentication Server.

dDot1xExtAuthBackendAuthFails.name: dDot1xExtAuthBackendAuthFails
dDot1xExtAuthBackendAuthFails.description: Counts the number of times that the state machine receives an EAP-Failure message from the Authentication Server (i.e., aFail becomes TRUE, causing a transition from RESPONSE to FAIL). Indicates that the Supplicant has not authenticated to the Authentication Server.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionStatsTable.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionStatsTable
dDot1xExtAuthSessionStatsTable.description: A table that contains the diagnostics objects for the Authenticator PAE associated with each Port/MAC/VLAN (for multi-auth mode).

dDot1xExtAuthSessionStatsEntry.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionStatsEntry
dDot1xExtAuthSessionStatsEntry.description: The statistics information for an Authenticator PAE, including multi-auth mode.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionMacAddr.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionMacAddr
dDot1xExtAuthSessionMacAddr.description: This object indicates the MAC address of the entry.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionVlanId.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionVlanId
dDot1xExtAuthSessionVlanId.description: This object indicates the VLAN ID of the entry.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionOctetsRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionOctetsRx
dDot1xExtAuthSessionOctetsRx.description: The number of octets received in user data frames on this Port during the session.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionOctetsTx.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionOctetsTx
dDot1xExtAuthSessionOctetsTx.description: The number of octets transmitted in user data frames on this Port during the session.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionFramesRx.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionFramesRx
dDot1xExtAuthSessionFramesRx.description: The number of user data frames received on this Port during the session.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionFramesTx.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionFramesTx
dDot1xExtAuthSessionFramesTx.description: The number of user data frames transmitted on this Port during the session.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionId.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionId
dDot1xExtAuthSessionId.description: A unique identifier for the session, in the form of a printable ASCII string of at least three characters.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionAuthenticMethod
dDot1xExtAuthSessionAuthenticMethod.description: The authentication method used to establish the session.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionTime.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionTime
dDot1xExtAuthSessionTime.description: The duration of the session in seconds.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionTerminateCause.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionTerminateCause
dDot1xExtAuthSessionTerminateCause.description: The reason for the session termination.

dDot1xExtAuthSessionUserName.name: dDot1xExtAuthSessionUserName
dDot1xExtAuthSessionUserName.description: The User-Name representing the identity of the Supplicant PAE.

dDot1xExtLoggedSuccess.name: dDot1xExtLoggedSuccess
dDot1xExtLoggedSuccess.description: The trap is sent when a host has successfully logged in (passed 802.1X authentication).

dDot1xExtLoggedFail.name: dDot1xExtLoggedFail
dDot1xExtLoggedFail.description: The trap is sent when a host failed to pass 802.1X authenitcation (login failed).

dDot1xExtCompliance.name: dDot1xExtCompliance
dDot1xExtCompliance.description: The compliance statement for entities which implement the DLINKSW-DOT1X-EXT-MIB.

dDot1xExtGeneralGroup.name: dDot1xExtGeneralGroup
dDot1xExtGeneralGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the global configuration for 802.1X extensions.

dDot1xExtPortIfGroup.name: dDot1xExtPortIfGroup
dDot1xExtPortIfGroup.description: A collection of objects providing the interface-specific information for 802.1X extensions.

ddot1xExtPaeAuthStatsGroup.name: ddot1xExtPaeAuthStatsGroup
ddot1xExtPaeAuthStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing statistics about an Authenticator PAE, including the multi-auth mode.

ddot1xExtPaeAuthDiagGroup.name: ddot1xExtPaeAuthDiagGroup
ddot1xExtPaeAuthDiagGroup.description: A collection of objects providing diagnostic statistics about an Authenticator PAE, including the multi-auth mode.

ddot1xExtPaeAuthSessionStatsGroup.name: ddot1xExtPaeAuthSessionStatsGroup
ddot1xExtPaeAuthSessionStatsGroup.description: A collection of objects providing statistics about the current, or last session for an Authenticator PAE, including the multi-auth mode.

ddot1xExtNotifyCfgGroup.name: ddot1xExtNotifyCfgGroup
ddot1xExtNotifyCfgGroup.description: A collection of objects provides the configuration for notification of 802.1X authentication.

dDot1xExtNotificationGroup.name: dDot1xExtNotificationGroup
dDot1xExtNotificationGroup.description: The collection of notifications used for monitoring the hosts under the control of 802.1X authentication.
